As NIGHTSHIFT tapped on the wall it appeared to be a normal wall made
of stone and rock huen out from the ground, typical for the type of
rock and sediment for this area. Reasonably strong, but something that
any of the MAXIMALS could either dig through or blow up given time.

WINDLORD and PERCEPTOR determine much the same thing. The stone around
the gates can be dug through by PERCEPTOR easilly enough, or if they
they wanted to use firepower they should be able to break the lock
with a few well placed shots.

At the same time the piece of the dart that was still embedded in
NIGHTSHIFT was begining to glow an odd silver color as NIGHTSHIFT lay
unconscious.

(TAG)
